That's the secant

00:03:33.070 --> 00:03:33.510
line.

00:03:33.510 --> 00:03:39.100
 

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:40.210
Just like that.

00:03:40.210 --> 00:03:45.510
This was the point over
here, the point 3,9.

00:03:45.510 --> 00:03:50.230
And then this point up here is
the point 3 plus delta x, so

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:54.340
just some larger number than
3, and then it's going to

00:03:54.340 --> 00:03:55.790
be that number squared.

00:03:55.790 --> 00:03:58.110
So it's going to be 3
plus delta x squared.

00:03:58.110 --> 00:03:59.070
What is that?

00:03:59.070 --> 00:04:01.310
That's going to be 9.

00:04:01.310 --> 00:04:03.720
I'm just foiling this out,
or you do the distribute

00:04:03.720 --> 00:04:04.940
property twice.

00:04:04.940 --> 00:04:09.280
a plus b squared is a squared
plus 2 a b plus b squared, so

00:04:09.280 --> 00:04:11.430
it's going to be 9 plus two
times the product

00:04:11.430 --> 00:04:12.020
of these things.

00:04:12.020 --> 00:04:17.345
So plus 6 delta x, and then
plus delta x squared.

00:04:17.345 --> 00:04:21.070
 

00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:22.530
That's the coordinate
of the second line.

00:04:22.530 --> 00:04:25.470
This looks complicated, but I
just took this x value and I

00:04:25.470 --> 00:04:29.230
squared it, because it's on the
line y is equal to x squared.

00:04:29.230 --> 00:04:32.430
So the slope of the secant

00:04:32.430 --> 00:04:35.500
line is going to be the
change in y divided

00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:37.050
by the change in x.

00:04:37.050 --> 00:04:42.500
So the change in y is just
going to be this guy's y value,

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:49.430
which is 9 plus 6 delta
x plus delta x squared.

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:52.610
That's this guy's y value,
minus this guy's y value.

00:04:52.610 --> 00:04:55.310
 

00:04:55.310 --> 00:04:58.000
So minus 9.

00:04:58.000 --> 00:04:59.510
That's your change in y.

00:04:59.510 --> 00:05:03.630
And you want to divide
that by your change in x.

00:05:03.630 --> 00:05:05.020
Well what is your change in x?

00:05:05.020 --> 00:05:07.210
This is actually going to
be pretty convenient.

00:05:07.210 --> 00:05:09.490
This larger x value-- we
started with this point on the

00:05:09.490 --> 00:05:11.460
top, so we have to start with
this point on the bottom.

00:05:11.460 --> 00:05:15.680
So it's going to be
3 plus delta x.

00:05:15.680 --> 00:05:17.340
And then what's this x value?

00:05:17.340 --> 00:05:20.700
What is minus 3?

00:05:20.700 --> 00:05:22.070
That's his x value.

00:05:22.070 --> 00:05:23.760
So what does this simplify to?

00:05:23.760 --> 00:05:27.020
The numerator-- this 9
and that 9 cancel out,

00:05:27.020 --> 00:05:28.320
we get a 9 minus 9.

00:05:28.320 --> 00:05:30.780
And in the denominator
what happens?

00:05:30.780 --> 00:05:32.560
This 3 and minus 3 cancel out.

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:35.550
So the change in x actually end
up becoming this delta x, which

00:05:35.550 --> 00:05:38.490
makes sense, because this delta
x is essentially how much more

00:05:38.490 --> 00:05:39.990
this guy is then that guy.

00:05:39.990 --> 00:05:43.360
So that should be the
change in x, delta x.

00:05:43.360 --> 00:05:44.810
So the slope of my secant

00:05:44.810 --> 00:05:53.860
