my change in x, plus my change

00:05:53.860 --> 00:06:00.130
in x squared, all of that
over my change in x.

00:06:00.130 --> 00:06:02.640
And now we can simplify
this even more.

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:05.140
Let's divide the numerator
and the denominator

00:06:05.140 --> 00:06:06.790
by our change in x.

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:09.900
And I'll switch colors just
to ease the monotony.

00:06:09.900 --> 00:06:13.110
So my slope of my
tangent of my secant

00:06:13.110 --> 00:06:15.580
line-- the one that goes
through both of these-- is

00:06:15.580 --> 00:06:17.483
going to be equal if you
divide the numerator and

00:06:17.483 --> 00:06:19.650
denominator this becomes 6.

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:21.420
I'm just dividing numerator
and denominator by delta

00:06:21.420 --> 00:06:26.130
x plus six plus delta x.

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:28.080
So that is the slope
of this secant

00:06:28.080 --> 00:06:34.630
line So slope is equal
to 6 plus delta x.

00:06:34.630 --> 00:06:36.280
That's this one right here.

